You kept your eyes
on it at every stop?

29:32.872 --> 29:34.271
As instructed.

29:41.346 --> 29:43.213
They'll take it from here.

29:43.348 --> 29:44.815
Good work, son.

29:51.490 --> 29:57.494
(soft piano music)

29:57.496 --> 30:07.571
♪

30:07.573 --> 30:22.185
♪

30:22.188 --> 30:27.190
<i> ♪ no one knows me</i>
<i> like the piano</i>

30:27.226 --> 30:29.192
<i> ♪ in my mother's home ♪</i>

30:29.195 --> 30:37.400
(lucy softly sobs)

30:37.469 --> 30:39.069
Hush now.

30:39.204 --> 30:42.005
<i> ♪ I have something</i>

30:42.074 --> 30:44.875
<i> ♪ some people</i>
<i> call it soul</i>

30:44.877 --> 30:49.312
(lucy softly sobs)

30:51.483 --> 30:56.953
<i> ♪ a new drive top the sky,</i>
<i> oh you'll arrive</i>

30:56.989 --> 30:59.422
<i> ♪ when I was</i>
<i> three years old ♪</i>

30:59.458 --> 31:04.994
(soft piano music)
(lucy softly sobs)

31:14.240 --> 31:27.718
♪

31:27.720 --> 31:30.386
Garvey:
<i> Fellow citizens of africa,</i>

31:30.422 --> 31:31.922
I greet you in the name of

31:31.924 --> 31:33.590
The united negro
improvement association.

31:33.725 --> 31:38.595
(applause and cheers)

31:40.099 --> 31:42.266
Garvey:
<i> We, of the united negro</i>
<i> improvement association,</i>

31:42.401 --> 31:45.802
<i> Are raising the cry for</i>
<i> africa for the africans,</i>

31:45.838 --> 31:48.204
<i> Those at home and</i>
<i> those abroad.</i>

31:48.274 --> 31:49.372
(applause and cheers)

31:49.408 --> 31:52.075
We seek to emancipate
the negro everywhere,

31:52.111 --> 31:53.276
Industrially,

31:53.279 --> 31:54.144
Educationally,

31:54.279 --> 31:55.211
<i> Politically</i>

31:55.247 --> 31:56.279
<i> And religiously.</i>

31:56.415 --> 32:00.016
<i> On going back to</i>
<i> our respective homes</i>

32:00.052 --> 32:03.586
We go with determination
to lay down, if needs be,

32:03.622 --> 32:07.190
<i> The last drop of our blood</i>
<i> for the defence of africa</i>

32:07.326 --> 32:09.026
And the emancipation
of our race.

32:09.161 --> 32:14.230
(cheers and applause)

32:14.266 --> 32:16.967
An insult was hurled at the
civilized negroes of the world

32:18.437 --> 32:20.170
When they took upon
themselves the right

32:20.172 --> 32:21.304
To parcel out a proportion

32:21.340 --> 32:24.874
Of 608,000 square miles
of our own land!

32:25.978 --> 32:28.011
For we have never
gave it up.

32:28.146 --> 32:29.645
We have never sold it.

32:29.682 --> 32:30.880
It was still ours.

32:30.916 --> 32:32.315
(audience cheering)

32:32.318 --> 32:34.918
Garvey:
<i> And we are the more aggrieved</i>

32:34.920 --> 32:36.252
Because of the lynch rope,

32:36.322 --> 32:37.587
Because of the segregation,

32:37.589 --> 32:40.190
Because of the jim crowism
that is used,

32:40.192 --> 32:42.259
Practiced and exercised
here in this country

32:42.261 --> 32:43.860
And in other parts
of the world

32:43.862 --> 32:45.762
By the white nations
of the earth,

32:45.897 --> 32:48.398
<i> Wherever negroes</i>
<i> happen accidentally</i>

32:48.467 --> 32:50.666
<i> Or otherwise to</i>
<i> find themselves.</i>

32:51.971 --> 32:54.871
If there's no safety for the
negroes in this white world,

32:55.007 --> 32:58.008
I cannot see what right they
have to parcel out the homeland,

32:58.143 --> 32:59.609
The country of the negroes.

32:59.678 --> 33:02.212
(applause and cheers)

33:02.214 --> 33:03.947
The world ought to
understand that the negro

33:03.949 --> 33:05.248
Has come to life,

33:05.317 --> 33:07.184
<i> Possessed with a</i>
<i> new conscience,</i>

33:07.319 --> 33:09.152
A new soul.

33:09.154 --> 33:11.354
I warn the world that
the day will come

33:11.357 --> 33:13.690
When the races of the world
will marshal themselves

33:13.825 --> 33:16.760
In great conflict for the
survival of the fittest.

33:16.762 --> 33:21.698
(applause and cheers)

33:27.372 --> 33:28.772
Marlene:
<i> Brother garvey!</i>

33:30.376 --> 33:31.541
Greetings, sister?

33:31.543 --> 33:33.510
Massey. Marlene massey.

33:33.579 --> 33:36.179
I am part of the u.N.I.A
chapter in montreal.

33:36.181 --> 33:37.280
Ah.

33:37.416 --> 33:40.650
Had a chance to visit
montreal about two years ago.

33:40.652 --> 33:42.085
Wonderful city.

33:43.022 --> 33:44.154
<i> You're doing</i>
<i> fine work there.</i>

33:44.289 --> 33:45.254
Keep it up.

33:45.290 --> 33:47.524
Actually,
that's why I came.

33:47.526 --> 33:49.692
I believe that we
could do more.

33:49.762 --> 33:52.062
<i> I have a plan for a clinic.</i>

33:52.131 --> 33:53.463
Black owned, black run,

33:53.499 --> 33:56.332
Serving the black
community in montreal.

33:56.368 --> 33:58.235
I like the sound
of it already.

33:58.370 --> 33:59.536
I found some
properties for rent,

33:59.538 --> 34:02.138
And I believe in a few years
we could be profitable.

34:04.543 --> 34:07.944
(soft music)

34:08.013 --> 34:10.146
Garvey:
<i> Those are highly</i>
<i> endorsed by mr. Powell.</i>

34:11.283 --> 34:12.282
He'll be speaking shortly,

34:12.417 --> 34:14.051
As one of the leaders
of the movement.

34:15.554 --> 34:17.287
You believe in eugenics?

34:18.623 --> 34:22.959
I endorse in the race purity
ideas mr. Powell purports,

34:23.095 --> 34:24.361
<i> The strength of</i>
<i> one's bloodline</i>

34:24.363 --> 34:26.362
<i> Is the strength</i>
<i> of one's race.</i>

34:26.398 --> 34:27.363
And we are,

34:27.433 --> 34:28.498
As you know,

34:28.633 --> 34:30.367
The original race.

34:30.369 --> 34:31.268
What about the part

34:31.403 --> 34:34.037
That sanctions the
sterilization of women

34:34.106 --> 34:36.706
Or getting rid of
"feeble-minded" individuals?

34:36.842 --> 34:39.575
Sister, have you never
pricked your soul

34:39.611 --> 34:41.511
On a thorn you found
reading scripture?

34:42.848 --> 34:45.314
Love someone whose
ways were unloving?

34:47.352 --> 34:50.253
<i> You may not agree with</i>
<i> all he stands for sister,</i>

34:50.388 --> 34:53.256
But one does not discard
the baby with the bathwater.

34:55.227 --> 34:57.127
I thank you for coming,
sister massey.

34:57.196 --> 34:58.128
And I'll be sure to speak
to your chapter head

34:58.263 --> 34:59.930
About the clinic.

35:00.599 --> 35:02.265
Excuse me-

35:02.267 --> 35:04.400
Garvey:
<i> Nice to see you and</i>
<i> thank you for coming.</i>

35:04.436 --> 35:10.473
(soft dramatic music)

35:10.476 --> 35:19.816
♪

35:19.951 --> 35:21.151
(door knocking)

35:23.355 --> 35:25.421
Zeke:
<i> Mr. Randolph?</i>

35:25.457 --> 35:27.824
<i> I don't know if</i>
<i> you remember me.</i>

35:27.826 --> 35:29.292
The porter with a plan?

35:29.294 --> 35:30.426
Zeke:
<i> Yes sir.</i>

35:30.496 --> 35:31.962
<i> Zeke garrett.</i>

35:32.698 --> 35:34.297
This isn't a great time.

35:34.333 --> 35:35.365
Zeke:
<i> Oh, right.</i>

35:35.434 --> 35:36.632
<i> I understand.</i>

35:36.768 --> 35:38.368
(tense music)

35:38.437 --> 35:39.769
I'll wait.

35:39.905 --> 35:45.709
(tense music)

35:45.844 --> 35:52.449
♪

35:52.451 --> 35:54.451
Zeke:
<i> Mr. Randolph,</i>
<i> I-I've been followed,</i>

35:54.453 --> 35:56.252
<i> Room broken into,</i>

35:56.388 --> 35:58.254
<i> Community garden</i>
<i> got destroyed,</i>

35:58.323 --> 36:00.256
<i> And someone is talkin'</i>
<i> to the company,</i>

36:00.292 --> 36:02.058
<i> Telling them my every move.</i>

36:02.060 --> 36:03.793
Randolph:
<i> Hmm.</i>

36:04.229 --> 36:05.328
Please.

36:06.298 --> 36:07.731
You've got a snitch.

36:07.866 --> 36:10.033
And in my experience,
snitches get paid.

36:11.369 --> 36:13.469
<i> So you need to find out</i>
<i> who the company is paying.</i>

36:13.505 --> 36:15.004
How do you suppose
I do that?

36:15.006 --> 36:16.439
You know what they say
about house slaves

36:16.508 --> 36:18.008
And field slaves?

36:18.143 --> 36:20.476
Folks think the house
slave is the, uh, uncle tom

36:20.512 --> 36:21.944
And the field slave
is the threat.

36:21.980 --> 36:23.613
But they have it all wrong.

36:23.748 --> 36:25.481
Well, how do you figure?

36:25.551 --> 36:27.484
The house slave was the
one making their food,

36:27.486 --> 36:28.751
Fixing their drinks,

36:28.753 --> 36:30.020
Making their beds at night.

36:30.155 --> 36:32.121
Well it sounds
like a porter.

36:32.191 --> 36:34.957
Don't underestimate the threat
you can be on the inside.

36:34.993 --> 36:36.692
<i> There's value to being</i>
<i> close to the enemy.</i>

36:36.728 --> 36:38.494
<i> Ears to the door, hmm?</i>

36:38.530 --> 36:40.096
Collecting information.

36:40.999 --> 36:42.632
So I should get
close to edwards?

36:42.634 --> 36:44.934
Build his trust.

36:44.937 --> 36:47.370
And when you have enough,
you get out

36:47.505 --> 36:48.805
And blow the whole thing up.

36:48.874 --> 36:51.407
(soft dramatic music)

36:51.476 --> 36:57.446
(background chatter)
(soft dramatic music)

36:57.482 --> 37:02.719
♪

37:02.721 --> 37:04.253
How you doin',
lucy-mae?

37:05.724 --> 37:07.257
Just getting ready to fade
back into the shadows

37:07.392 --> 37:09.059
Of the back row.

37:15.534 --> 37:16.800
You know, back
when I told people

37:16.935 --> 37:20.403
That I was gonna
open this joint,

37:20.405 --> 37:22.338
They thought that
I was crazy.

37:25.744 --> 37:28.144
Couldn't imagine that a black
man could do much around here

37:28.180 --> 37:31.614
Except, you know,
work in the mines,

37:31.617 --> 37:33.083
On the trains.

37:34.419 --> 37:35.818
What's that
gotta do with me?

37:37.956 --> 37:39.155
Just because people
weren't understanding

37:39.224 --> 37:41.624
What you were bringin',

37:41.627 --> 37:43.326
Don't mean it wasn't good.

37:49.334 --> 37:51.301
So you're saying I
can keep headlining?

37:53.438 --> 37:55.204
I want you to be
my stage director.

37:56.608 --> 37:57.440
Hmm?

37:57.575 --> 37:59.308
Come up with the routines.

38:00.512 --> 38:03.546
Let's give these folks a,
a taste for the future.

38:04.582 --> 38:06.015
But slowly.

38:07.753 --> 38:09.252
A taste for the future?

38:11.456 --> 38:13.456
Well that's a new
way of puttin' it.

38:13.591 --> 38:16.125
All you're really sayin'
is stay in the back row.

38:16.194 --> 38:18.461
This crowd don't
deal in coal.

38:18.463 --> 38:19.729
Jigaboo, tar baby,

38:19.765 --> 38:21.397
Ink stain, eight-rock.

38:21.433 --> 38:23.133
I've heard it all before.

38:29.474 --> 38:31.474
I'm only gonna
say this once,

38:32.877 --> 38:34.377
So listen up.

38:36.681 --> 38:39.149
<i> You got something that none</i>
<i> of these other girls got.</i>

38:40.619 --> 38:42.551
Girl, that is vision.

38:46.624 --> 38:47.757
<i> So I'm gonna leave it</i>
<i> up to you to decide</i>

38:47.793 --> 38:49.492
<i> What you wanna</i>
<i> do with it.</i>

39:02.641 --> 39:04.974
(engine rumbling)

39:05.010 --> 39:06.976
Marlene:
<i> Every page is</i>
<i> full of nonsense,</i>

39:07.012 --> 39:10.380
<i> Like restrictive immigration</i>
<i> and selective breeding.</i>

39:12.084 --> 39:15.251
Zeke:
<i> Yeah, well, he ain't</i>
<i> alone in his thinkin'.</i>

39:15.253 --> 39:16.853
<i> I mean, you could hardly find</i>
<i> a copy of that book anywhere.</i>

39:16.855 --> 39:20.256
Marlene:
<i> They call them "socially</i>
<i> inadequate persons".</i>

39:20.325 --> 39:21.824
<i> You should see the list:</i>

39:22.661 --> 39:24.127
The wayward,

39:24.129 --> 39:26.863
Deaf, deformed, dependent.

39:26.932 --> 39:29.599
And they always blame the
"deficiency" on the mother.

39:29.668 --> 39:30.667
Well you know
nothin' like that

39:30.669 --> 39:32.935
Will ever happen
to teddy, right?

39:32.937 --> 39:34.604
Not as long as
I'm breathing.

39:34.739 --> 39:36.206
(zeke softly chuckles)

39:36.341 --> 39:38.674
I have half of mind to go home
and build that clinic myself.

39:38.710 --> 39:40.410
(softly laughs) go on, marlene.

39:40.545 --> 39:42.212
Marlene:
<i> I'm serious, zeke!</i>

39:42.347 --> 39:44.013
<i> I am through asking</i>
<i> for permission.</i>

39:44.082 --> 39:46.849
<i> I'm gonna get my clinic</i>
<i> one way or another.</i>

39:50.221 --> 39:51.421
Paperwork.

39:56.161 --> 39:58.661
On the first page is
a list of all my kin,

39:58.697 --> 40:00.863
Ah, dates of birth.

40:00.932 --> 40:03.633
And how do I know you
didn't make this all up?

40:03.768 --> 40:05.835
Well, why would I do that?

40:06.971 --> 40:08.705
Looks to me this nigger's

40:08.840 --> 40:12.509
<i> Trying to smuggle in his</i>
<i> prostitute in his fancy car.</i>

40:13.845 --> 40:20.416
I'm a porter with the
cross continental railroad, sir.

40:20.452 --> 40:24.554
<i> And the company</i>
<i> gave us this card</i>

40:24.623 --> 40:26.388
When we crossin' the border.

40:29.861 --> 40:31.527
Said you're a porter, huh?

40:31.596 --> 40:32.761
That's right.

40:34.599 --> 40:36.398
I'll take a shine
before you go.

40:36.435 --> 40:40.803
(tense music)

40:40.872 --> 40:44.941
But I'm off duty, sir,
and I don't got my kit.

40:44.943 --> 40:47.510
Oh, spit shine'll
do just fine.

40:49.815 --> 40:52.548
<i> Or maybe you'd rather</i>
<i> I take your lady aside</i>

40:52.617 --> 40:54.416
And conduct a
thorough inspection

40:54.453 --> 40:57.287
<i> To make sure she's not</i>
<i> bringing in any impurities.</i>

40:57.422 --> 41:03.293
(tense music)

41:03.428 --> 41:15.572
♪

41:15.707 --> 41:16.906
Harrison:
<i> See?</i>

41:17.843 --> 41:19.275
<i> I just did half your work.</i>

41:22.347 --> 41:23.846
Hurry up.

41:23.849 --> 41:29.852
(tense dramatic music)

41:29.855 --> 41:39.662
♪

41:39.664 --> 41:45.401
♪

41:45.470 --> 41:48.070
(engine revving)

41:48.106 --> 41:54.076
(tense dramatic music)

41:54.112 --> 41:58.748
♪

41:58.817 --> 42:00.750
Marlene:
<i> Zeke, slow down.</i>

42:00.885 --> 42:01.784
<i> Zeke.</i>

42:01.853 --> 42:03.619
(tires squealing)

42:03.621 --> 42:04.787
Zeke, stop!

42:07.459 --> 42:09.225
(horn honking)

42:09.360 --> 42:10.593
Marlene:
<i> What are you doing?</i>

42:10.662 --> 42:11.894
(horn honking)

42:11.897 --> 42:14.830
(tense dramatic music)

42:14.866 --> 42:16.298
Zeke!

42:16.334 --> 42:18.100
<i> You're scaring me, zeke!</i>

42:18.136 --> 42:24.173
(tense dramatic music)

42:24.175 --> 42:25.842
♪

42:25.977 --> 42:27.443
(door slams)

42:31.716 --> 42:33.148
(zeke screams)

42:35.387 --> 42:37.853
(zeke pants)

42:54.172 --> 43:01.077
(cicada hums)
(wind rustles)

43:11.756 --> 43:16.659
(voices clamouring)

43:27.972 --> 43:29.038
Zeke.

43:35.847 --> 43:37.113
I'll see you tomorrow.

43:41.686 --> 43:42.851
Hey marlene?

43:46.057 --> 43:47.823
Junior didn't ask
me to take you.

43:49.394 --> 43:50.325
What?

43:50.362 --> 43:51.326
(soft music)

43:51.363 --> 43:52.662
I know, I-I-I'm sorry.

43:52.797 --> 43:55.030
I just know how much it
meant to you and I just-

43:56.201 --> 43:58.067
I just couldn't stand to
see your dreams slip away.

44:00.405 --> 44:01.871
Thank you.

44:01.940 --> 44:07.844
(soft music)

44:07.979 --> 44:18.154
♪

44:18.223 --> 44:21.157
(lift humming)

44:33.004 --> 44:35.705
The watch and the money should
more than cover this week.

44:37.942 --> 44:40.043
Something happen I
should know about?

44:40.178 --> 44:41.944
Nothing that's
gonna happen again.

44:41.946 --> 44:44.313
I don't see any
blood on your hands.

44:44.449 --> 44:45.581
Which leads me to believe

44:45.583 --> 44:46.849
Whatever problem
you encountered,

44:46.984 --> 44:48.383
You failed to solve.

44:56.961 --> 44:58.461
<i> In this business-</i>

44:58.596 --> 45:01.564
(tense dramatic music)

45:01.566 --> 45:03.565
Queenie:
<i> The only way</i>
<i> you can be sure</i>

45:03.601 --> 45:06.535
You won't encounter
the same problem twice.

45:06.537 --> 45:09.404
(tense dramatic music)

45:09.441 --> 45:11.640
(blade slicing)
(bobby gasping)

45:11.676 --> 45:13.342
(bobby gurgling)

45:13.478 --> 45:17.714
(tense dramatic music swells)

45:21.319 --> 45:23.886
(bobby gurgling)

45:28.293 --> 45:34.230
(suspenseful music)

45:34.299 --> 45:37.133
♪

45:37.268 --> 45:41.937
This is what bobby did
with his second chance.

45:48.045 --> 45:50.379
Same hustle,
different drug.

45:54.185 --> 45:56.919
The last man who
stole from me

45:57.054 --> 45:59.588
Got picked out of the
river piece by piece.

46:01.025 --> 46:04.393
Believe me, porter,
this was a kindness.

46:04.529 --> 46:07.730
(ominous music)

46:07.865 --> 46:09.131
If you leave a
man breathing,

46:09.200 --> 46:11.066
You leave him with another
chance to betray you.

46:12.937 --> 46:14.937
So you know what you
have to do, right?

46:15.072 --> 46:19.007
(tense dramatic music)

46:19.043 --> 46:21.344
Hmm.

46:21.479 --> 46:23.078
Sticks, clean this bitch up.

46:23.080 --> 46:28.984
(tense dramatic music)

46:29.053 --> 46:37.560
♪

46:37.562 --> 46:40.796
(train chugging)

46:40.832 --> 46:44.833
(clock ticking)

46:50.708 --> 46:51.641
Mr. Edwards.

46:51.776 --> 46:52.975
Mr. Garrett?

46:53.044 --> 46:56.279
<i> Earlier today I had some</i>
<i> trouble crossing the border.</i>

46:56.281 --> 47:01.049
The customs agent, well,
the way he spoke to me.

47:01.085 --> 47:02.985
Didn't you have your card?

47:03.120 --> 47:05.187
<i> See, well, that's just it.</i>

47:05.256 --> 47:06.789
As soon as I
showed it to him,

47:06.924 --> 47:08.991
All of a sudden I was
able to get right through.

47:10.061 --> 47:12.461
<i> And it made me</i>
<i> realize how valued</i>

47:12.463 --> 47:14.930
Being a porter on your
railway really is.

47:16.501 --> 47:17.733
And I just wanted
to apologize

47:17.802 --> 47:20.102
For ever taking that
for granted, sir.

47:20.138 --> 47:22.538
Good to see you've come to
your senses, mr. Garrett.

47:22.607 --> 47:25.508
I think we could work together
to make things better, sir.

47:29.146 --> 47:31.948
Sir, I would appreciate
if you would consider

47:31.950 --> 47:33.349
Appointing me to the
welfare committee.

47:33.351 --> 47:34.683
The welfare committee?

47:34.752 --> 47:36.085
<i> Yes, sir.</i>

47:36.154 --> 47:37.286
If it's all right with you,

47:37.355 --> 47:39.488
I would like to be the head
man between your office

